In [54]:



     


def fit_model(df, model_name):
    """
    Method to fit the data with various models
    """
    X = df.iloc[:,:-1]
    y = df.iloc[:,-1]
    
    if model_name == 'LR':
        model = LogisticRegression(random_state=1, solver='liblinear')
    elif model_name == 'DT':
        model = tree.DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=1)
    elif model_name == 'SVM':
        model = SVC(kernel='poly', random_state=1)
    elif model_name == 'RF':
        model = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=1)
    elif model_name == 'NB':
        model = GaussianNB()
        
    k = 10
    cv = KFold(n_splits=k, random_state=1, shuffle=True)
    
    accuracy = cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv = cv)
    auc = cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv = cv, scoring="roc_auc")
    
    return (accuracy.mean(), auc.mean())

from numpy import interp

# random forest revisited
def fit_random_forest(df):
    X = df.iloc[:,:-1]
    y = df.iloc[:,-1]
    
    accuracy_list = []
    auc_list = []
    tprs = []
    
    k = 10
    cv = KFold(n_splits=k, random_state=1, shuffle=True)
    mean_fpr = np.linspace(0,1,100)
    
    model = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=1)

    i = 1
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,7))
    
    for train, test in cv.split(X, y):
        X_train, X_test = X.iloc[train], X.iloc[test]
        y_train, y_test = y.iloc[train], y.iloc[test]
        
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        y_pred = model.predict(X_train)
        y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        y_pred_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
        
        fpr, tpr,_ = metrics.roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
        roc_auc_test = metrics.auc(fpr, tpr)
        accuracy = metrics.accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred)
        
        auc_list.append(roc_auc_test)
        accuracy_list.append(accuracy)
        tprs.append(interp(mean_fpr, fpr, tpr))
        
        
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, lw=2, alpha=0.3, label='ROC fold %d (AUC = %0.2f)' % (i, roc_auc_test))
        plt.legend(loc=4)
        i= i+1
        
    
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],linestyle = '--',lw = 2,color = 'black')
    mean_tpr = np.mean(tprs, axis=0)
    mean_auc = metrics.auc(mean_fpr, mean_tpr)
    plt.plot(mean_fpr, mean_tpr, color='blue', label=r'Mean ROC (AUC = %0.2f )' % (mean_auc),lw=2, alpha=1)
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('ROC')
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.show()
    
    return mean_auc

# for different test set

def fit_random_forest_test_set(df, test_df):
    X = df.iloc[:,:-1]
    y = df.iloc[:,-1]
    
    X_test = test_df.iloc[:,:-1]
    y_test = test_df.iloc[:,-1]
    
    accuracy_list = []
    auc_list = []
    tprs = []
    
    k = 10
    cv = KFold(n_splits=k, random_state=1, shuffle=True)
    mean_fpr = np.linspace(0,1,100)
    
    model = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=1)

    i = 1
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,7))
    
    for train, test in cv.split(X, y):
        X_train = X.iloc[train]
        y_train = y.iloc[train]
                
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        y_pred = model.predict(X_train)
        y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        y_pred_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
        
        fpr, tpr,_ = metrics.roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
        roc_auc_test = metrics.auc(fpr, tpr)
        accuracy = metrics.accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred)
        
        auc_list.append(roc_auc_test)
        accuracy_list.append(accuracy)
        tprs.append(interp(mean_fpr, fpr, tpr))
        
        
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, lw=2, alpha=0.3, label='ROC fold %d (AUC = %0.2f)' % (i, roc_auc_test))
        plt.legend(loc=4)
        i= i+1
        
    
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],linestyle = '--',lw = 2,color = 'black')
    mean_tpr = np.mean(tprs, axis=0)
    mean_auc = metrics.auc(mean_fpr, mean_tpr)
    plt.plot(mean_fpr, mean_tpr, color='blue', label=r'Mean ROC (AUC = %0.2f )' % (mean_auc),lw=2, alpha=1)
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('ROC')
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.show()
    
    return mean_auc
